The paper deals with solving inverse problems in image processing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is a key aspect of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The iterative nature of the proposed method involves making successive estimates, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with blind estimation of the measurement process, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
